#11701
Welcome to Amethyst Mud School, learning to walk~
&WThis is a service I have decided to provide since I've had so many people
come in here and not know how to talk or move or anything.  So we'll
be going through it bit by bit, then hopefully you'll know enough commands
to be able to move about the academy without dying a hundred times.
The first thing to know is that a mud like Amethyst consists of lots
of "rooms", which basically are seperated by "exits", the exits are
usually seen after looking at the room description, and they are the
basic north, northeast, east, southeast, south, southwest, west, northwest,
down and up.  These can be done with simply n, ne, e, se, s, sw, w, nw,
d, and u, respctively.  Sometimes you will come across exits that aren't
so simple, being either hidden or using a keyword, such as in town at
the gate you will type "gate" to leave through gate, and if you come
across a crack in a wall by typing "crack".  See "&OHELP MOVEMENT&W"
for more movement information.
There is a single exit in this room, please move forward now.
~
