#11703
Learning to speak/use channels~
&WSee "&OHELP SAY&W" and "&OHELP CHANNELS&W" for information on speach
and channels.
Basically "say" is used to communicate with people only in the same
room as you.  To talk to someone specific and privatly who is or isn't
in the same room as you, use the command "tell" and 'reply".
Channels are public, and spamming them, i.e. repeating a message several
times or anything absurd such as bad language has penalties.  Again,
looking at "&OHELP CHANNELS&W" will teach you to turn off and on certain
channels, and how to use them and what each one is for.
~
