#11704
Learning to use/search for the help topics~
&WJust about every single thing you would ever need to know is located
in a help file, the hard part sometimes is finding the correct one.
Using the command "&OCOMMANDS&W" gives a full list of available commands,
also related is "&OSOCIALS&W" which gives expressive commands.
For commands, simple type "&OHELP &W<full command name>"
If you don't know specifically what you are looking for, try using the
command "hlist", see "&OHELP HLIST&W".  This will allow you to search
through several help files and you'll possibly be able to find it by
yourself.  With all of these options unable to help you, try using a
channel such as "ask" or "newbiechat".  When all else fails, then you
can ask an immortal for assistance, and we appreciate players taking
things into their own matters before asking us.
~
